content: Just turned 22 in the city that never sleeps. Reflecting on the past year, I see a path of growth despite the setbacks. Today, I'm focusing on refining my trading algorithms with a new AI tool I've been learning.
Had a promising meeting with a mentor from my last job. Got some insights on how blockchain can revolutionize trading. Planning to dive deep into this space.
After a month of research, I've crafted a trading strategy that leverages blockchain's transparency. Met with a local startup to pitch my idea. Fingers crossed!
The startup was interested but wanted more proof of concept. Back to the drawing board to refine my algorithms with blockchain integration.
Found a bug in my trading algorithm that was skewing my risk assessment. Fixed it, but it's a reminder of the importance of thorough testing.
Joined a local meetup for tech enthusiasts. Shared my blockchain trading idea and got some fantastic feedback. Networking is key in this city.
I've been working on a new AI model for personalized trading. The results are promising, but it's a slow process. Every day brings me closer to a breakthrough.
Had a setback. My latest algorithm failed in a live simulation. It's back to the drawing board, but these failures are just steps towards success.
Met with a former colleague who introduced me to a quant firm looking for talent. Submitted my application, now waiting for a response.
I'm attending a seminar on AI in finance next week. Hoping to gain insights and maybe connect with potential employers or partners.
The seminar was insightful. Made some connections and got an interview lined up with the quant firm. Fingers crossed for this opportunity.
Interview went well! They're impressed with my blockchain trading idea. Now, I'm preparing a more detailed pitch for the next round.
Received feedback on my trading strategy from a peer. Integrating their suggestions, which feels like fine-tuning a piano for the perfect sound.
Finally, got an offer from the quant firm! Negotiating terms now. This could be the big break I've been working towards.
As the year ends, I'm reflecting on how much I've learned from the challenges I faced. Ready to start at the quant firm next month. Here's to new beginnings and continued growth.
